; Lower-stratum negated view fixture (checkpoint (d), analysis sec 4.5 R9).
;
; The negated view (blk) sits STRICTLY LOWER in the stratification than the
; pred row it gates: the pred (mid) is derived through an EXTRA hop
; (raw -> step -> mid) so mid's stratum is above blk's. The oracle picks
; per-rule atom order by strata (Convention B: negated-atom-first when the
; negated view is lower), while the runtime uses global convention A. This
; fixture pins the A-vs-B OBSERVATIONAL EQUIVALENCE: both must produce the
; same published out set on every batch, including the differential blk flip.
;
; raw(K, V)   : feed(K, V).            base
; step(K, V)  : raw(K, V).             extra hop (lifts mid a stratum)
; mid(K, V)   : step(K, V).            the pred, now strictly above blk
; blk(K)      : block(K).              the negated view (lower stratum)
; out(K, V)   : mid(K, V), !blk(K).    negate: pred above, negated below
#message feed(u64 K, u64 V).
#message block(u64 K) @differential.

#local raw(u64 K, u64 V).
#local step(u64 K, u64 V).
#local mid(u64 K, u64 V).
#local blk(u64 K).

#query out(free u64 K, free u64 V).

raw(K, V) : feed(K, V).
step(K, V) : raw(K, V).
mid(K, V) : step(K, V).
blk(K) : block(K).

out(K, V) : mid(K, V), !blk(K).
